1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 29-01 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to law enforcement use of a drone or robot.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 29-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Use of drones and robots.
7 1. A law enforcement officer may not use a drone or robot to:
8 a. Issue or serve an arrest warrant or summons in lieu of a warrant upon complaint
9 under Rule 4 of the North Dakota Rules of Criminal Procedure ;
10 b. Take an individual into custody in the manner authorized by law to answer for the
11 commission of an offense;
12 c. Conduct hostage negotiations;
13 d. Manage traffic;
14 e. Gather evidence of a crime without a warrant; or
15 f. Monitor public events without a warrant.
16 2. This section does not apply to the use of a drone or robot for search and rescue of a
17 missing individual, disposal of a bomb, or crime scene analysis.
